---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout lang="en" title="Method">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Method</h1>
    <p>This project implements a verifiable information pipeline: collect candidate papers from primary sources, rank them with a multi-signal rules engine, generate bilingual daily briefs, and expose candidate-level scoring on source pages.</p>
    <h2>Collection</h2>
    <p>The default collector covers AI-related arXiv categories including cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MA, cs.IR, cs.RO, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.DC, stat.ML, and eess.AS. Categories and limits are configuration-driven.</p>
    <h2>Scoring Signals</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Institution background from configured top institutions.</li>
      <li>Community recommendation through optional HF Daily Papers enrichment.</li>
      <li>Community heat through HF upvote tiers.</li>
      <li>Top conference signals such as NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, ACL, and CVPR.</li>
      <li>Code availability through paper text or GitHub metadata.</li>
      <li>Practitioner relevance keywords such as deployment, inference, agents, RAG, safety, and evaluation.</li>
      <li>Academic impact through optional Semantic Scholar citation counts.</li>
      <li>Open-source heat through optional GitHub stars and trending signals.</li>
      <li>arXiv category weight from configured AI categories.</li>
      <li>Novelty and duplicate penalties for repeated titles.</li>
      <li>Recent topic repetition penalties to reduce consecutive same-topic concentration.</li>
      <li>Safety, ethics, and governance keywords for additional visibility.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Cadence</h2>
    <p>The default cadence is T+2: the site publishes every day at 07:12 Beijing/Taipei time and normally collects, scores, and briefs arXiv papers from two days earlier. Without external API keys, production runs continue with arXiv metadata; mock-run is reserved for fixed demo data and offline validation.</p>
    <h2>Transparency</h2>
    <p>Every issue has a source page listing all candidates, selection tiers, total scores, score breakdowns, matched keywords, external signals, and degradation warnings.</p>
    <h2>Limits</h2>
    <p>Briefs are generated from titles, abstracts, and public metadata by default. They do not replace full-paper reading, and arXiv preprints must not be described as verified conclusions or conference acceptances.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
